
    Usage: sonda [options]

    Options:

        -r | --recommends   Check required and recommended system settings
        -v | --version      Display the version of the Sonda tool
        -u | --update       Update the Sonda tool to the latest version
        
        -s | -sys           Show system information (CPU, memory, devices, etc.)
        -n | -net           Show network information (interfaces, active connections, etc.)

        -G | -sysnet        Combines -s and -n output for both system and network information

        -v <LEVEL>          Set the verbosity level for output (values 1-8, with 1 being minimal and 8 being maximum)

        -all                Show all available system and network information (long output)
        -ald                Show detailed system and network information (very long output)

        -battery            Show battery status and power information
        -cpu                Show detailed CPU information
        -devices            Show information about PCI and USB devices
        -disks*             Show disk and storage information (requires sudo for detailed partition info)
        -gpu                Show GPU and graphics card information
        -kernel             Show kernel boot parameters and loaded modules
        -memory*            Show memory information (requires sudo for detailed memory usage)
        -network            Show detailed information about network interfaces and active connections
        -packages           List all installed packages

        --SAVE              Save the output to a log file (currently disabled)
